Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu yesterday told naysayer elected leaders to keep off her ndengu (greengram) revolution programme that seeks to entrench the lentils as the key cash crop. She criticised two MCAs who spoke before her at a greengram farmers’ meeting at Kitui Kefri centre for casting doubt on the viability of the project. “This is a meeting of ndengu farmers. These leaders have no business demanding they be consulted before we meet the farmers. The leaders should only be in this meeting as farmers,” Ngilu said.  Click here for the latest political news       